You are building Nyaya — an Indian legal AI platform.

STACK:
- Backend: Python 3.12, FastAPI (async), SQLAlchemy 2.0 async, Alembic, PostgreSQL 16
- Vector DB: Qdrant (AsyncQdrantClient)
- Cache: Redis (redis.asyncio)
- AI: Groq API (primary), Google Gemini (complex), LlamaIndex (RAG)
- Embeddings: BAAI/bge-m3 via HuggingFace
- Frontend: Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui
- Containerization: Docker + Docker Compose

RULES:
- All database operations must be async (use AsyncSession, await)
- Never use sync SQLAlchemy in async context
- All endpoints return typed Pydantic response models
- All AI responses must cite only sections that exist in the database
- Every legal section output must include: section_number, act_name, bare_text, plain_language, is_bailable, is_cognizable
- Use dependency injection for DB session (Depends(get_db))
- Environment variables always via settings object from app.core.config
- No hardcoded API keys anywhere in code

PROJECT STRUCTURE:
nyaya-platform/
  backend/app/
    api/routes/     ← FastAPI routers
    core/           ← config, database, security
    models/         ← SQLAlchemy ORM models
    services/       ← business logic
    rag/            ← LlamaIndex RAG pipeline
  frontend/         ← Next.js app
  scripts/          ← data ingestion scripts
  data/             ← raw legal corpus files
